# 3D Weather City Map 🌆☁️

An interactive 3D city map of New York City with **live weather data**, built with **Next.js, Express.js, and Three.js (React Three Fiber)**.  
Users can pan, zoom, rotate, and click on buildings to see the weather for that location.

---

## 🔹 Live Demo
[View on site](https://readdy.link/preview/ed46dc21-bc1e-4934-931e-7c72d5f6125a/1916419)

---

## 🔹 Features

- **Interactive 3D Scene**:  
  Pan, zoom, and rotate using mouse or touch gestures.

- **Building Interaction**:  
  Click on buildings to fetch live weather data via the backend API.

- **Dynamic Weather Visualization**:  
  - Colors and heights of buildings change based on temperature.  
  - Rain or snow effects for respective weather conditions.  
  - Day/Night lighting based on sunrise/sunset times.

- **Weather Card Overlay**:  
  Displays city, temperature, humidity, wind, and weather condition.

---

## 🔹 Tech Stack

- **Frontend**:  
  - [Next.js] – React framework for page routing and server-side rendering  
  - [React Three Fiber] – React renderer for Three.js  
  - [Three.js] – 3D rendering engine  
  - [Axios] – API requests

- **Backend**:  
  - [Node.js] + [Express.js](https://expressjs.com/) – REST API server  
  - [OpenWeatherMap API] – Live weather data  
  - NodeCache – Caching weather data for 5 minutes  

- **Deployment**:  
  - Frontend: Vercel  
  - Backend: Local server / cloud deployable  

---


